AGI - It is the MSC Aries the ship captured by the Iranian authorities in the Persian Gulf. The Italian-Switzerland group announced it, adding that on board the container there are 25 crew members. Foreign Minister Tajani has specified that there are no Italians on board. "We are sorry to confirm that the MSC Aries... has been boarded by the Iranian authorities by helicopter while crossing the Strait of Hormuz around 4.43 Italian time" we read in a note of the group, "we are working closely with the competent authorities to ensure the welfare of the crew and the safe return of the ship". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
The White House invited Iran to release the seized ship immediately, while tensions in the Middle East increase and increase fears of a Tehran attack of retaliation against Israel. "We call on Iran to immediately release the ship and its international crew," said the national Security Council spokesman, Adrienne Watson. "Sequesting a civil ship without provocation is a blatant violation of international law and an act of piracy by the body of the guards of the Islamic revolution".
&nbsp;
The United States reiterated "full support" to Israel against attacks by Iran, during a call between US Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin and Israeli Defense Minister Yoav Gallant. It's a note from the U.S. Department of Defense. Lloyd, the Pentagon explains, "discussed regional urgent threats and reiterated the unwavering US support for Israel's defence." "Austin - we read in the note - made it clear that Israel can count on full American support in the defense of Israel against all attacks by Iran and its allies in the region."
&nbsp;
US president, Joe Biden, interrupted his weekend in Delaware to return to Washington for urgent consultations on the Middle East, told the White House. Iran announced retaliation after an alleged Israeli attack on 1 April razed a building of Iranian diplomacy in Damascus, where seven members of the Elite revolutionary Guards were killed, including two generals. "The president will return to the White House this afternoon to consult with his national security team on events in the Middle East," said the White House.&nbsp;
