Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan> decided to respond to the allegations raised on social media: in the last few weeks the messages in which Turkey was accused of doing business with the Jewish State, forgetting the Palestinian population. The dissemination of this information contributed to the collapse of the Erdogan party in the administrative elections on 31 March. Before October 7 and the beginning of the Turkey and Israel conflict had normalized diplomatic relations after a decade of controversy and accusations. The long history of tensions between the two countries, which has always been caused by Israeli policies towards the Palestinians, has not affected trade. This time things have gone differently and since last October some chains of Israeli supermarkets have blocked the import of Turkish products and in general, according to official data, trade between the two countries had already dropped by 33% before sanctions.&nbsp;
